The paper deals with algorithms for computing sparse solutions to least-squares problems, which are commonly used in numerical analysis and optimization. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the use of truncated SVD, which is a common technique in information theory. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as sparse solutions are commonly used in machine learning algorithms. The paper also involves data structures (cs.DS) as it discusses algorithms for computing sparse solutions. Finally, the paper involves social and information networks (cs.SI) as sparse solutions are commonly used in network analysis.
